{% set pageTitle = "Tile pattern" %}
{% set pageSection = "Design system" %}
{% set subSection = "Components" %}
{% set pageDescription = "Use Tile pattern as decorative component chrome when a design needs the OFH tile motif." %}
{% set theme = "Component primitives" %}
{% set dateUpdated = "July 2026" %}

{% extends "app-layout.njk" %}

{% block breadcrumb %}
  {% include "../_breadcrumb.njk" %}
{% endblock %}

{% block bodyContent %}

  <p>Use Tile pattern as a decorative primitive inside another component. It does not hold content, add interaction, or decide where it appears in the layout.</p>
  <p>Components must pass the exact matrix they need. There is no default pattern. Use Figma tile numbers <code>1</code> to <code>22</code>, and use <code>null</code> for an empty tile.</p>

  {{ designExample({
    group: "components",
    item: "tile-pattern",
    type: "default"
  }) }}

  <h2 id="colour">Colour</h2>
  <p>Use <code>color</code> in code. The available values are <code>brand</code>, <code>accent</code>, <code>accent-light</code>, <code>white</code>, and <code>transparent</code>. Individual tiles can override the pattern colour.</p>
  <p><code>accent</code> and <code>accent-light</code> use theme-aware accent tokens, so they change with the participant or research theme bundle. <code>brand</code>, <code>white</code>, and <code>transparent</code> are fixed colours.</p>
  <p><code>transparent</code> renders a transparent tile; <code>null</code> is the empty/off tile.</p>

  <h2 id="size">Size</h2>
  <p>Tiles default to <code>120px</code>. Use <code>tileSize</code> when a component needs a smaller or larger pattern.</p>

  {{ designExample({
    group: "components",
    item: "tile-pattern",
    type: "compact"
  }) }}

{% endblock %}
